---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Marteso Blog — ASO Tips, Growth Guides & Product Updates"
  description="Practical App Store Optimization guides, keyword strategy tips, A/B testing insights, and Marteso product updates. Written by the team behind 2.4M+ tracked keywords."
  activeNav="blog"
  canonicalPath="/blog"
>
  <div class="page-header">
    <div class="page-header-inner">
      <div>
        <div class="section-label">Blog</div>
        <h1>ASO insights &amp; product updates</h1>
      </div>
      <div class="category-filter">
        <a href="#" class="cat-pill active">All</a>
        <a href="#" class="cat-pill">ASO</a>
        <a href="#" class="cat-pill">Growth</a>
        <a href="#" class="cat-pill">Product</a>
        <a href="#" class="cat-pill">Guides</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="blog-section">
    <a href="#" class="featured-post">
      <div class="post-thumbnail">
        <div class="thumb-illustration">
          <div class="thumb-bar accent"></div>
          <div class="thumb-bar" style="width:90%"></div>
          <div class="thumb-bar" style="width:75%"></div>
          <div class="thumb-bar blue-accent" style="margin-top:8px"></div>
          <div class="thumb-bar blue" style="width:80%"></div>
          <div class="thumb-bar blue" style="width:65%"></div>
          <div class="thumb-bar" style="width:55%;margin-top:8px"></div>
          <div class="thumb-bar accent" style="width:38%"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="post-content">
        <div class="post-meta">
          <span class="post-category cat-aso">ASO</span>
          <span class="post-date">March 5, 2026</span>
        </div>
        <h2>How to pick keywords that actually rank in 2026</h2>
        <p>The App Store algorithm has changed significantly over the past 18 months. Here's the exact keyword selection framework we recommend — backed by data from 2.4 million tracked keywords.</p>
        <div class="post-author">
          <div class="author-avatar">LK</div>
          <span class="author-name">Lena K.</span>
          <span class="read-time">· 8 min read</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </a>

    <div class="posts-grid">
      <a href="#" class="post-card">
        <div class="card-thumb">
          <div style="display:flex;align-items:flex-end;gap:6px;height:80px;">
            <div style="width:18px;height:40%;background:var(--accent-dim);border-radius:3px 3px 0 0;"></div>
            <div style="width:18px;height:60%;background:var(--accent-dim);border-radius:3px 3px 0 0;"></div>
            <div style="width:18px;height:80%;background:var(--accent);border-radius:3px 3px 0 0;"></div>
            <div style="width:18px;height:90%;background:var(--accent);border-radius:3px 3px 0 0;"></div>
            <div style="width:18px;height:75%;background:var(--accent-dim);border-radius:3px 3px 0 0;"></div>
            <div style="width:18px;height:95%;background:var(--accent);border-radius:3px 3px 0 0;"></div>
            <div style="width:18px;height:85%;background:var(--accent-dim);border-radius:3px 3px 0 0;"></div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
          <div class="post-meta"><span class="post-category cat-growth">Growth</span><span class="post-date">Feb 26, 2026</span></div>
          <h3>The 60-day ASO playbook: from launch to top charts</h3>
          <p>A step-by-step roadmap for new apps: what to focus on in weeks 1–2, 3–6, and 7–12 to build momentum in the rankings.</p>
          <div class="card-footer">
            <div class="post-author"><div class="author-avatar" style="width:24px;height:24px;font-size:11px;">MR</div><span class="author-name">Marc R.</span></div>
            <span class="read-time">12 min</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </a>

      <a href="#" class="post-card">
        <div class="card-thumb">
          <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:8px;width:100%;padding:4px;">
            <div style="background:var(--accent-blue-dim);border:1px solid rgba(94,106,210,0.2);border-radius:6px;padding:10px;text-align:center;"><div style="font-size:11px;color:var(--accent-blue);font-weight:600;margin-bottom:4px;">A</div><div style="font-size:16px;font-weight:700;">31.2%</div></div>
            <div style="background:rgba(74,222,128,0.08);border:1px solid rgba(74,222,128,0.25);border-radius:6px;padding:10px;text-align:center;"><div style="font-size:11px;color:#4ade80;font-weight:600;margin-bottom:4px;">B ★</div><div style="font-size:16px;font-weight:700;color:#4ade80;">38.9%</div></div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
          <div class="post-meta"><span class="post-category cat-guide">Guide</span><span class="post-date">Feb 18, 2026</span></div>
          <h3>A/B testing your app icon: what we learned from 200+ experiments</h3>
          <p>Icon tests consistently show the highest conversion lift of any store listing element. Here's what works, what doesn't, and how to read the data correctly.</p>
          <div class="card-footer">
            <div class="post-author"><div class="author-avatar" style="width:24px;height:24px;font-size:11px;">JB</div><span class="author-name">Julia B.</span></div>
            <span class="read-time">9 min</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </a>

      <a href="#" class="post-card">
        <div class="card-thumb">
          <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:6px;width:100%;padding:4px;">
            <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;"><div style="width:8px;height:8px;border-radius:50%;background:#4ade80;flex-shrink:0;"></div><div style="height:6px;border-radius:3px;background:rgba(74,222,128,0.3);flex:1;"></div><span style="font-size:10px;color:#4ade80;font-weight:600;">72%</span></div>
            <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;"><div style="width:8px;height:8px;border-radius:50%;background:var(--accent-blue);flex-shrink:0;"></div><div style="height:6px;border-radius:3px;background:var(--accent-blue-dim);width:25%;"></div><span style="font-size:10px;color:var(--accent-blue);font-weight:600;">18%</span></div>
            <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:8px;"><div style="width:8px;height:8px;border-radius:50%;background:var(--accent);flex-shrink:0;"></div><div style="height:6px;border-radius:3px;background:var(--accent-dim);width:13%;"></div><span style="font-size:10px;color:var(--accent);font-weight:600;">10%</span></div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
          <div class="post-meta"><span class="post-category cat-aso">ASO</span><span class="post-date">Feb 10, 2026</span></div>
          <h3>How to use review sentiment to prioritize your product backlog</h3>
          <p>Your reviews are a goldmine of product intelligence. Here's how to systematically extract actionable insights from thousands of reviews each month.</p>
          <div class="card-footer">
            <div class="post-author"><div class="author-avatar" style="width:24px;height:24px;font-size:11px;">LK</div><span class="author-name">Lena K.</span></div>
            <span class="read-time">7 min</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </a>

      <a href="#" class="post-card">
        <div class="card-thumb">
          <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:6px;width:100%;padding:4px;">
            <div style="background:var(--bg-primary);border:1px solid var(--border);border-radius:6px;padding:8px 10px;"><div style="font-size:11px;font-weight:700;color:var(--text-primary);margin-bottom:2px;">Focus Flow – Productivity</div><div style="font-size:10px;color:var(--text-tertiary);">Title · 30 chars · ✓</div></div>
            <div style="background:var(--bg-primary);border:1px solid rgba(94,106,210,0.3);border-radius:6px;padding:8px 10px;"><div style="font-size:11px;font-weight:700;color:var(--accent-blue);margin-bottom:2px;">AI suggestion</div><div style="font-size:10px;color:var(--text-tertiary);">"Focus Flow: Task Manager Pro"</div></div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
          <div class="post-meta"><span class="post-category cat-guide">Guide</span><span class="post-date">Jan 30, 2026</span></div>
          <h3>Writing App Store titles that rank and convert</h3>
          <p>Your 30-character title is the single most impactful ASO lever you have. Here's how to use every character strategically without keyword stuffing.</p>
          <div class="card-footer">
            <div class="post-author"><div class="author-avatar" style="width:24px;height:24px;font-size:11px;">MR</div><span class="author-name">Marc R.</span></div>
            <span class="read-time">6 min</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </a>

      <a href="#" class="post-card">
        <div class="card-thumb" style="flex-direction:column;gap:8px;">
          <div style="display:flex;justify-content:space-between;width:100%;padding:4px;">
            <div style="text-align:center;"><div style="font-size:18px;font-weight:700;color:var(--accent);">#3</div><div style="font-size:10px;color:var(--text-tertiary);">My App</div></div>
            <div style="text-align:center;"><div style="font-size:18px;font-weight:700;color:var(--text-secondary);">#7</div><div style="font-size:10px;color:var(--text-tertiary);">Competitor A</div></div>
            <div style="text-align:center;"><div style="font-size:18px;font-weight:700;color:var(--text-tertiary);">#12</div><div style="font-size:10px;color:var(--text-tertiary);">Competitor B</div></div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
          <div class="post-meta"><span class="post-category cat-growth">Growth</span><span class="post-date">Jan 22, 2026</span></div>
          <h3>Competitor keyword research: a step-by-step framework</h3>
          <p>How to systematically analyze what your top competitors rank for — and identify the gaps you can fill in your next metadata update.</p>
          <div class="card-footer">
            <div class="post-author"><div class="author-avatar" style="width:24px;height:24px;font-size:11px;">JB</div><span class="author-name">Julia B.</span></div>
            <span class="read-time">11 min</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </a>

      <a href="#" class="post-card">
        <div class="card-thumb">
          <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:6px;width:100%;padding:4px;">
            <div style="font-size:11px;color:var(--text-tertiary);margin-bottom:4px;">Organic installs · 90 days</div>
            <div style="display:flex;align-items:flex-end;gap:3px;height:60px;">
              <div style="flex:1;background:var(--accent-dim);border-radius:2px 2px 0 0;height:30%"></div>
              <div style="flex:1;background:var(--accent-dim);border-radius:2px 2px 0 0;height:40%"></div>
              <div style="flex:1;background:var(--accent-dim);border-radius:2px 2px 0 0;height:50%"></div>
              <div style="flex:1;background:var(--accent-dim);border-radius:2px 2px 0 0;height:60%"></div>
              <div style="flex:1;background:var(--accent);border-radius:2px 2px 0 0;height:72%"></div>
              <div style="flex:1;background:var(--accent);border-radius:2px 2px 0 0;height:85%"></div>
              <div style="flex:1;background:var(--accent);border-radius:2px 2px 0 0;height:100%"></div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="card-body">
          <div class="post-meta"><span class="post-category cat-product">Product</span><span class="post-date">Jan 10, 2026</span></div>
          <h3>Introducing Marteso v1.7: Autonomous Mode</h3>
          <p>Our biggest release yet: Autonomous Mode lets Marteso proactively surface opportunities and draft actions for you to approve — without replacing your judgment.</p>
          <div class="card-footer">
            <div class="post-author"><div class="author-avatar" style="width:24px;height:24px;font-size:11px;">AP</div><span class="author-name">Marteso Team</span></div>
            <span class="read-time">5 min</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <section class="newsletter">
    <div class="newsletter-card">
      <div class="newsletter-text">
        <h2>Get ASO insights in your inbox</h2>
        <p>One email per week. Practical tips, case studies, and Marteso updates.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="newsletter-form">
        <input type="email" class="newsletter-input" placeholder="you@example.com" />
        <a href="#" class="btn btn-primary btn-large">Subscribe</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .page-header {
    padding: 120px 32px 64px;
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 64px auto 0;
  }

  .page-header-inner {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: flex-end;
  }

  h1 { font-size: 48px; margin-bottom: 0; }

  .category-filter {
    display: flex;
    gap: 8px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .cat-pill {
    padding: 6px 14px;
    border-radius: 100px;
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    text-decoration: none;
    background: var(--bg-secondary);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    transition: all 0.2s;
  }

  .cat-pill:hover, .cat-pill.active {
    color: var(--text-primary);
    border-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.15);
  }

  .blog-section {
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto 80px;
    padding: 0 32px;
  }

  /* Featured post */
  .featured-post {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 64px;
    align-items: center;
    background: var(--bg-secondary);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 48px;
    text-decoration: none;
    margin-bottom: 32px;
    transition: border-color 0.2s;
  }

  .featured-post:hover { border-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); }

  .post-thumbnail {
    background: var(--bg-tertiary);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 32px;
    min-height: 200px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .thumb-illustration { width: 100%; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 6px; }

  .thumb-bar {
    height: 8px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    background: var(--border);
    width: 100%;
  }

  .thumb-bar.accent { background: rgba(234,14,43,0.4); }
  .thumb-bar.blue-accent { background: rgba(94,106,210,0.5); }
  .thumb-bar.blue { background: rgba(94,106,210,0.25); }

  .post-meta { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px; margin-bottom: 12px; }

  .post-category {
    font-size: 11px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    padding: 3px 8px;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }

  .cat-aso { background: var(--accent-dim); color: var(--accent); }
  .cat-growth { background: rgba(74,222,128,0.12); color: #4ade80; }
  .cat-product { background: var(--accent-blue-dim); color: var(--accent-blue); }
  .cat-guide { background: rgba(251,191,36,0.12); color: #fbbf24; }

  .post-date { font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-tertiary); }

  .featured-post h2 {
    font-size: 26px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin-bottom: 12px;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    line-height: 1.3;
  }

  .featured-post p {
    font-size: 15px;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }

  .post-author {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 8px;
  }

  .author-avatar {
    width: 32px;
    height: 32px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--accent-dim);
    color: var(--accent);
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 700;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .author-name { font-size: 13px; font-weight: 500; }
  .read-time { font-size: 13px; color: var(--text-tertiary); }

  /* Posts grid */
  .posts-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 16px;
  }

  .post-card {
    background: var(--bg-secondary);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 10px;
    overflow: hidden;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: border-color 0.2s;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }

  .post-card:hover { border-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.15); }

  .card-thumb {
    height: 120px;
    background: var(--bg-tertiary);
    padding: 16px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  .card-body {
    padding: 20px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    flex: 1;
  }

  .card-body h3 {
    font-size: 15px;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: 8px;
    line-height: 1.4;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .card-body p {
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    flex: 1;
  }

  .card-footer {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    margin-top: auto;
  }

  /* Newsletter */
  .newsletter {
    max-width: 1200px;
    margin: 0 auto 120px;
    padding: 0 32px;
  }

  .newsletter-card {
    background: var(--bg-secondary);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 48px;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 48px;
  }

  .newsletter-text h2 {
    font-size: 24px;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin-bottom: 8px;
  }

  .newsletter-text p {
    font-size: 15px;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  .newsletter-form {
    display: flex;
    gap: 12px;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .newsletter-input {
    background: var(--bg-primary);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 10px 16px;
    font-size: 15px;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    width: 240px;
    outline: none;
    transition: border-color 0.2s;
  }

  .newsletter-input:focus { border-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.2); }
  .newsletter-input::placeholder { color: var(--text-tertiary); }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .page-header-inner { flex-direction: column; align-items: flex-start; gap: 24px; }
    .featured-post { grid-template-columns: 1fr; gap: 32px; }
    .posts-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .newsletter-card { flex-direction: column; }
    .newsletter-form { flex-direction: column; width: 100%; }
    .newsletter-input { width: 100%; }
  }
</style>
